citation.db_name: Tau degradation: the ubiquitin-proteasome system versus the autophagy-lysosome system.

links.evidence: The mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR) kinase negatively modulates autophagy by phosphorylating Atg1, an autophagy initiating factor, while adenosine monophosphate-activated protein kinase (AMPK), a major sensor for the cellular energy status, activates autophagy through inhibiting mTOR signaling as well as by direct phosphorylation of Atg1 (Egan et al., 2011; Kim et al., 2011). Increased mTOR activity results in autophagy downregulation and tau accumulation.
